items.title: Harper shows signs of progress in knee rehab
items.summary: Bryce Harper is beginning to make small strides of progress in his recovery from an injured left knee, an encouraging sign for the Nationals as they hope to get the star outfielder back for the postseason. Harper jogged around the warning track at Nationals Park, along with a team trainer, prior to Wednesday's game against the Braves.

items.summary: The Indians have now put together a winning streak that feels as big and memorable and historic, in their sport, as the Lakers winning 33 in a row in pro basketball in 1971.

items.title: Indians' streak compared with other sports
items.summary: The Tribe notched its 21st consecutive victory on Wednesday, defeating the Tigers, 5-3, at Progressive Field, to pass the 2002 A's for a new AL record. Here is a look at how the Indians' streak stacks up against the best in other major American sports.

items.title: Tribe's 'Streak' makes you feel alive
items.summary: The Indians, you might have heard, have won 21 consecutive baseball games -- the most recent a 5-3 victory over the Tigers at Progressive Field on Wednesday afternoon in a game sealed by a diving Lonnie Chisenhall catch, a postseason-worthy roar from the 29,346 in attendance and goosebumps from anybody with a sporting soul.
